## Experiment Setup

Dataset: SNAP Pokec with processed benchmark features from `pokec.mat`.

Task: binary node classification with chronological registration-year split.

Split:

| split | nodes |
| --- | ---: |
| train | 1,218,296 |
| valid | 297,038 |
| test | 117,306 |

Graph:

- Main training graph: undirected+self-loop
- Preprocessing follows the paper-style/tunedGNN convention: `to_undirected`, remove self-loops, then add self-loops
- Training edges including self-loops: 46,236,731
- Raw directed edges: 30,622,564

Features/classes:

- Nodes: 1,632,803
- Features: 65
- Classes: 2

Model setting:

| parameter | value |
| --- | ---: |
| hidden channels | 256 |
| local GCN layers | 7 |
| residual connections | enabled |
| batch normalization | enabled |
| dropout | 0.2 |
| input dropout | 0.0 |
| learning rate | 0.0005 |
| weight decay | 0.0 |
| batch size | 250,000 |
| epochs | 100 |
| seeds | 1, 2, 3 |
| eval schedule | every 5 epochs after epoch 50 |
| directed graph | false |
| GSMP placement | first GCN layer only |
| GSMP self-loops | excluded from timestamp counts; self-loop weight 1.0 |

The GCN architecture was aligned to the large-graph paper implementation: 7 hidden GCN layers followed by a separate linear prediction head.

